// The Spear of White Ash +3 (IWD)                                       //
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
@11404 = ~The Spear of White Ash +3~
@11405 = ~Consecrated by Malarite priests hundreds of years ago, this spear was used on High Hunts in preparation for their bloody feasts. It was last in the hands of Old Hunter Wellin, who is believed to have died when he foolishly hunted dryads near the Cloakwood. The weapon is made from a single piece of ash wood topped with a cruel spearhead.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
- 5% of all hits cause an additional 1d6 points of piercing damage from the barbs on the spearhead

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+3
